IBM Corporation Announces Working With Las Vegas Metropolitan Police Department (LVMPD) To Help Improve City's Public Safety And Secure Information Sharing

Wednesday, 25 Jan 2012 09:01am EST

IBM Corporation announced that it is working with the Las Vegas Metropolitan Police Department (LVMPD) to help improve the city's public safety and secure information sharing with the agency's regional partners. Used by more than 3,000 law enforcement agencies across the U.S., IBM's i2 crime analytics software will enable LVMPD officers to accelerate their investigations by enabling them to make non-obvious connections based on information that was previously spread across the department.Â 

